bug.short_desc: Implemented a plugin system for job triggers in generator

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 888 Diff of tool/pylib/generator/Generator.py to integrate plugins
A zipped file is attached. It is self explanatory.

Created attachment 889 tool/pylib/plugins directory
... with configuration files and one example: process-json resource
Thomas, please review the patch and give us feedback.
The patch is incomplete, therefore unusable. (E.g. required modules yapsy.VersionedPluginManager, yapsy.IPlugin missing).
*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of bug 3692 ***

Created attachment 891 yapsy !
Yapsy added as a zip...

Created attachment 892 Lang.diff as it has not been fixed dynamically
needs to be fixed dynamically!

(In reply to comment #5) > Created attachment 891 [details] > yapsy ! > > Yapsy added as a zip...
It seems this attachment contains unattributed third-party code: - http://yapsy.sourceforge.net/ - authors Thibauld Nion et al. - BSD license

should I interpret it as you do not like non-copyleft software license?
Is there any specific reason for that other than copyleft protects freedom for all users?
No problem for us, we can replace it with the simple plugin system we developed ourselves, but still fullfiling the criterias in your previous discussion. Then there is no BSD at all and it is light weight.
Yapsy is medium weight but of course could be regarded as over weight for the task you had in mind....:-)

(In reply to comment #9) > should I interpret it as you do not like non-copyleft software license?
No problem with other licenses per se. But uploading the code as if it were your own, with an empty LICENSE file and without proper attribution, is a copyright infringement and a form of plagiarism which we strongly object. Besides, it violates all forms of netiquette in the open-source world which we are proud to be a member of.

Big words. I think there is space for cooling down now!
>But uploading the code as if it were your own,
We have not uploaded any code without copyright license or have said that there is code belonging to us which we don't own.
>with an empty LICENSE file and without proper attribution,
The yapsy lib is with coyright license. There is no empty license file. The package is zipped as it is downloaded from the yapsy page. We have not made any changes at all.
> is a copyright infringement and a form of plagiarism which we strongly object.
Strong accusations! Be careful what you say!
>Besides, it violates all forms of netiquette in the open-source world which we are proud to be a member of.
Also strong accusations! Be careful what you say!
You seem to love to fight for nothing! Did you forget that we were sharing an integration of yapsy to be able to use plugins for the generator?

(In reply to comment #11) > The yapsy lib is with coyright license. There is no empty license file.
This is simply not true, as anyone can see.

I don't know what you are talking about but it is irrelevant now.
We downloaded the yapsy lib zip as it was from their site and unzipped it. We have not changed a single byte in the yapsy directory.

Created attachment 898 Original Yapsi-1.8 download archive
Just for comparison, here is the *real* yapsy download, as featured on their SourceForge project site (http://sourceforge.net/projects/yapsy/files/Yapsy-1.8/Yapsy-1.8.tar.gz/download).
Even if you only downloaded the .egg file (http://sourceforge.net/projects/yapsy/files/Yapsy-1.8/Yapsy-1.8-py2.6.egg/download), it would have contained the EGG-INFO, with project url, author and license info. But even that is missing from your attachment, which in contrast contains the empty LICENSE file.

You are stubborn I think!
(In reply to comment #14) > Created attachment 898 [details] > Original Yapsi-1.8 download archive > > Just for comparison, here is the *real* yapsy download, as featured on their > SourceForge project site > (http://sourceforge.net/projects/yapsy/files/Yapsy-1.8/Yapsy-1.8.tar.gz/download).
This was the one we downloaded. When we do it now there is NO license file!!!
;-)
I have attached a screenshot from the package manager in Fedora. Can you see any License file??? ;-)
> Even if you only downloaded the .egg file > (http://sourceforge.net/projects/yapsy/files/Yapsy-1.8/Yapsy-1.8-py2.6.egg/download), > it would have contained the EGG-INFO, with project url, author and license > info. But even that is missing from your attachment, which in contrast contains > the empty LICENSE file.

Created attachment 899 Screenshot from Yapsy download!!!! ;-)
We can not see any LICENSE file! ;-)

(In reply to comment #15) > I have attached a screenshot from the package manager in Fedora. Can you see > any License file??? ;-)
This exactly shows that what you have uploaded to the bug was something else, and this is all that matters here.

You are talking! We have shown that we have not tried to or have any interest to change any package or license info. Your accusations are pointless!
I prefer you ask us next time instead of accusing! And if there is something wrong then, which it was not this time except your pointless accusations, we will of course change it.
Thank you!
